		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Darkfever&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I have a lvl 55 necro.  I love him.  I cannot quit playing him.  Necros are such a bad ass class, its not even funny how good we are lol.  Anyway, most necros solo most of their lives.  I have done the same although in some cases like in DL i would group up.  Most people dont know how useful we can be in grps and that frustrates me.  Although in some cases I have made people say damn necros are very good in grps.  I just like soloing for money and exp reasons..  I talk in guild chat and im the goofball of the guild cuz i am always talkin when waiting for spawn to pop etc..  I am the powerful one, i am the one who dont need a group.  I am the one who can do great in a grp if given the chance.  Our lvl 56 pet is a monster.  (i dont want to hear anything about mage pets better here, i know that, but listen to this)He hits for 59 Dual weilds, lifetaps like mad for 40-50 a pop,flying kicks for 71, and has duel attack.  Not to mention the lvl 55 buff we get for pet gives 65% haste, 60 str, and some ac.  This pet is a very very good damage dealer. Not to mention in upper lvls we get a grp mana tap that gives 300 mana to each grp member and has a 1 sec recast time. It does stack. :).. We also get a grp lifetap that heals each member for 720 hps over 48 secs..  Listen a necro is a very versatile class.  If your lookin for an extra grp member try us out, we are very useful..  Trust me geez.  If not oh well then i guess its your loss..  Im out...</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Sphoenix Darkfever</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" cla