		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, May 30th 10:53 PM2002 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=14&mid=102257415779797&num=3&post=1&replyto=102281298797907"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=102281298797907></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=166531"><span id=Scholar>VampiricFrenzy</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br />25 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.33]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=VampiricFrenzy&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Well, I think that it is common knowledge that a good, balanced group has abilities to do four things.<br />1. Deal damage<br />2. Heal damage dealers<br />3. Control mobs<br />4. Speed up damage dealing and upgrade damage dealers and slow down and decrease mob damage dealing<br /><br />Warriors and Monks can do the first. Clerics can obviously do the second. Chanters can do the third. And shamans are usually used to do the fourth. a good group would use two tanks, a healer, a chanter, and a shaman. That is only five spots, what should be the sixth spot be? My personal opinion is that it should go to the necro. A necro can do almost all of the above except the fourth. this makes them very versatile. They can mez if chanter cant handle it for some reasons, heal if cleric goes down, and the pet may taunt mobs off if the warrior is takin too much hits. I think however, that the reason why necros are often not taken over another tank is because most necros arent very good at adapting to different situations. Most solo most their lives and really can't muti-task at once. A lot of necros are behind on learning how to do group work when they are in dungeons because exp come very easy to them from soloing. once they hit the big levels, they have to learn to mez one creature then pump a heal to the warrior while making sure that the pet attacks the same creature that the main tank is hitting and keeping lich on, while watching his/her own health. On top of that, if the mob isn't getting killed fast enough, the necro needs to stack a couple of DoTs. A lot of pre 55 necros cast only four spells to level, darkness, fear, DoT life drain and one other DoT. Once they experience group, they are suddenly required to cast 6 to 7 different spells to be useful. The Necro is a supporter of the people that do the 4 things the best, which means that a lot of the times, they have to support mutiple players at once. It also means that they may have to support different people in differnt battles to truly be useful. What I am coming to is that, While Necros can be one of the best classes to have in a group due to the class's ability to help out mutiple aspects of a balanced group, It is very difficult to find a Necro that knows what he/she is doing to maximize the Necro's usefulness in a Group. Time is better spent finding another tank so that mobs can be downed faster so the main tanks won't require as much healing. Maybe as time goes on more quality Necros will become more available for everyone to see a necro's purpose in Group. One other good thing about having a necro in a group is that he/she supports, but requires no support. he drains to heal him/herself, and he does not run low on mana because he/she has his/her own clarity. He/she needs no protection because he/she has feign death. There are only advantages of having a Necro in a group as long as he/she knows what he/she is doing and not cast fear in a dungeon...   </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
